Thanks for the careful eye. One nuance: code/gaming_analyzer.py currently exp=
ects a richer `history` structure (per-iteration archive snapshots and evalua=
tion lists). The demo scripts emit a compact archive + per-iteration metrics =
but not the per-iteration archive payloads.

Two options:
- Quick path: Use code/experiment_analysis.py on the current outputs (it cove=
rs divergence, stuffing density, temporal trends). This works with the existi=
ng JSON structure from the demos.
- Full analyzer path: I can add an optional `--log-history` mode to the demos=
 that records lightweight per-iteration archive snapshots (docstrings + minim=
al scores), and a small adapter to emit the `history` field the analyzer expe=
cts. That enables judge correlation matrices and gaming_intensity directly fr=
om code/gaming_analyzer.py.

If you=E2=80=99re good with it, I=E2=80=99ll add `--log-history` and a tiny a=
dapter so the analyzer plugs in cleanly.
